README – Evidence Analysis
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates digital evidence analysis and chain-of-custody management using simulated data. The objective is to analyze network activity from a Windows system and identify suspicious connections while ensuring proper documentation of collected evidence.

🎯 Objective
Analyze system network connections
Identify suspicious activity
Maintain proper chain-of-custody
Ensure integrity of digital evidence
🧰 Tools Used
Velociraptor (simulated query execution)
FTK Imager (conceptual evidence handling)
🔍 Evidence Analysis

A simulated Velociraptor query was used:

SELECT * FROM netstat;
🖥️ Findings

The following suspicious connection was identified:

Local IP: 192.168.56.10
Remote IP: 185.220.101.45
Port: 443
Status: ESTABLISHED
🚨 Reason for Suspicion:
External IP not recognized
Matches known anonymized / suspicious network ranges
Unusual connection pattern
📊 Chain of Custody
Item	Description	Collected By	Date	Hash Value
Network Log	Server-Z Log	SOC Analyst	2025-04-09	fa0114d6f68fc9ce78f8c2a5042b337d8c905ff75
🔐 Evidence Integrity
Hash value generated using SHA256
Ensures no tampering of evidence
Maintains forensic validity
🧠 Conclusion

The analysis identified a suspicious external connection, indicating possible unauthorized communication. Proper documentation and hashing ensured the integrity of collected evidence. Continuous monitoring and investigation of unknown connections are essential to prevent potential security incidents.
